      <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="63.0" layoutY="100.0" prefHeight="495.0" prefWidth="870.0" text="PREPARING THE AGUA:BIT FOR (FIRST) USE&#10;After unpacking your Agua:Bit and installing the software found here: https://github.com/Nrojt/Agua-bit-companion-app, plug the Agua:Bit into your computer, open the application and go to the Update screen (on first startup the menu should be hidden, click on the three dots in the upper-left corner to reveal the menu). If this is your first time, make sure you are connected to the internet and press the &quot;Update&quot; or &quot;Download&quot;  button. The required file for the Agua:Bit will be downloaded to your documents folder. After the download is done, press the &quot;Update&quot; button again and the file will be uploaded to the Agua:Bit. The Agua:Bit can now be used.&#10;&#10;Plug the required sensors into the slots on the Agua:Bit and make sure they are firmly seated. Be careful when connecting the sensors, too much preasure can break either the sensor or the connector on the Agua:Bit.&#10;&#10;YOUR FIRST MEASUREMENT&#10;Head over to the Connect tab and select the sensors you connected to the Agua:Bit. Make sure to select the correct slots and the corresponding options. The slot numbers go from left to right. After your selection, press the &quot;Send to Agua:Bit&quot; button and wait until the confirmation message appears.&#10;&#10;Put the sensors into the water, for more information about the correct use of each sensor see our website, but make sure the Agua:Bit and its connection points stays dry. To make a measurement, go to the Measure tab and click &quot;Measure&quot;. The measured values should now appear on the screen.&#10;&#10;SAVING AND OPENING YOUR MEASUREMENT&#10;After taking a measurement, press the &quot;Save&quot; button to save your measurement. Give it a name, and if you want to, add the location and date of the measurement. Press &quot;Save&quot; again to save your measurement.&#10;&#10;To open your saved measurement(s), click on the &quot;Open measurement&quot; button. All locally saved measurements will appear on the left, and all measurements saved in our database will appear on the right. Select a measurement and click on the corresponding &quot;Open&quot; button to open the measurement.&#10;&#10;Take note: to save measurements in our database, a free account is required.&#10;&#10;LOG IN OR CREATE AN ACCOUNT&#10;In the app, click on the &quot;Login&quot; button in the menu. If you already have an account, fill in your email and password to log in. If you do not have an account yet, click on the &quot;Sign up&quot;  button. The fields on the left are required to make an account, the fields on the left are optional, but will enhance your experience and might be necessary for optional and/or future features. " wrapText="true" AnchorPane.bottomAnchor="20.0" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="20.0" AnchorPane.rightAnchor="20.0" AnchorPane.topAnchor="80.0" />
